Key Takeaways:

Optimal partition count depends on cluster size and data volume (rule of thumb: 2-4× CPU cores)
Caching dramatically improves performance for reused datasets but consumes memory
Always benchmark with realistic data volumes
Monitor Spark UI to identify bottlenecks
